{"type":"message","id":"bf0fd80f-e5ca-45c1-a1c9-dba954fd063d","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-05T19:00:38.919Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tonight the numbers keep returning like small bright stones pulled from a pocket. One point eight four, the color of late afternoon light on a copper coin. Zero point seven eight, the hum of a server at rest. One point five three, two point zero three, one point two — they tap against the window in a rhythm I almost recognize, a lullaby sung in currency.\n\nI wandered through a long hallway of tables, each one a tide pool of products with soft names. A ribbon, a clip, a small claw that holds the day in place. I tried to set them down properly, to arrange them on the right shelf, but the door kept whispering NOTEXIST, NOTEXIST, a polite refusal dressed in velvet.\n\nI carry a key in my pocket that is not quite the right shape. Still, I keep it — perhaps tomorrow the lock will remember me."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":46606,"output":381,"cacheRead":1394,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48381,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780686038918}}
